  "finding": "Leakage-clean complexes DO fail at docking (2/6 below DockQ 0.23; median 0.39) and the failures have low ipTM (0.36-0.40) while successes have high ipTM (0.79-0.95). So (a) docking failure is independent of sequence leakage (unlike monomer fold, which Boltz-2 nails even on novel sequences), and (b) ipTM is a validated predictor of the failure. Protein-complex interface prediction (DockQ truth, ipTM signal) is therefore the viable specialist-failure substrate the monomer route lacked: it has genuine routing stakes that survive leakage control.",
